results.name: Number of terms in inverse set of usigma = sum of unitary divisors = A034448.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: usigma(x)=288, invusigma(288)={138,154,165,168,213,235,248,253}, so a(288)=8, the number of all terms in the inverse set.
